Create the following three enums in loanflow-common under src/main/java/com/loanflow/common/enums. These are the API contract versions used in DTOs. The loan-service entity layer has its own JPA-annotated enums under com.loanflow.loanservice.entity.enums — keep them separate; the mapper converts between them.

LoanType.java:
public enum LoanType { PERSONAL, AUTO, MORTGAGE, BUSINESS }

LoanStatus.java:
public enum LoanStatus { SUBMITTED, PENDING_DOCUMENTS, UNDERWRITING_IN_PROGRESS, PENDING_REVIEW, APPROVED, REJECTED }

EmploymentStatus.java:
public enum EmploymentStatus { FULL_TIME, PART_TIME, SELF_EMPLOYED, UNEMPLOYED, RETIRED }

No @Enumerated, @Column, or any jakarta.persistence annotations.

