@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class LoanApplicationServiceImpl implements LoanApplicationService {

    @Override
    public CreateLoanApplicationResponse createApplication(
            CreateLoanApplicationRequest request, Long applicantUserId) {
        return CreateLoanApplicationResponse.builder()
            .applicationId(50021L)
            .status(LoanStatus.SUBMITTED)
            .submittedAt(Instant.now())
            .loanType(request.getLoanType())
            .amount(request.getAmount())
            .nextStep("UPLOAD_REQUIRED_DOCUMENTS")
            .build();
    }
}

The stub echoes loanType and amount from the incoming request so the response is traceable to the input. Import LoanStatus and LoanType from com.loanflow.common.enums.

Create com.loanflow.loanservice.controller.LoanApplicationController in loan-service:

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/applications")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class LoanApplicationController {

    private final LoanApplicationService loanApplicationService;

    @PostMapping
    @PreAuthorize("hasRole('APPLICANT')")
    public ResponseEntity<CreateLoanApplicationResponse> createApplication(
            @RequestBody @Valid CreateLoanApplicationRequest request,
            @AuthenticationPrincipal Jwt jwt) {
        Long applicantUserId = jwt.getClaim("userId");
        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED)
                .body(loanApplicationService.createApplication(request, applicantUserId));
    }
}

Create com.loanflow.loanservice.config.SecurityConfig in loan-service:

@Configuration
@EnableMethodSecurity
public class SecurityConfig {

    @Bean
    public SecurityFilterChain filterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        return http
            .csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())
            .sessionManagement(sm -> sm.sessionCreationPolicy(SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS))
            .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
                .requestMatchers("/actuator/health").permitAll()
                .anyRequest().authenticated())
            .oauth2ResourceServer(oauth2 -> oauth2.jwt(Customizer.withDefaults()))
            .build();
    }
}

Ensure the following are present in backend/loan-service/pom.xml (versions managed by loanflow-parent):
- spring-boot-starter-security
- spring-boot-starter-oauth2-resource-server

In application-dev.yaml set a local HMAC secret so JWT validation works without a running identity-service:

spring:
  security:
    oauth2:
      resourceserver:
        jwt:
          secret: dev-local-secret-key-min-32-chars
